<subSubSection id="A8D0653DFEDDFEBB5889F94AFE7466ED" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E07536B6FEDDFEBB5889F94AFE7466ED" blockId="272.[151,1436,1482,1940]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FEDDFEBB5913F94BFE4F6798" author="Rondani, C." box="[269,508,1734,1761]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 64)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FEDDFEBB5A64F94BFCD26799" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" box="[634,865,1734,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Volucella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alchimista">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FEDDFEBB5A64F94BFCD26799" box="[634,865,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Volucella alchimista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FEDDFEBB58EDF967FEFA667D" box="[243,329,1770,1796]" family="Number" pageId="272" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens, from material collected in South America by V. Ghiliani. 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FEDDFEBB5D42F967FE8F6651" author="Costa, A." pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">Costa (1866: 31)</bibRefCitation>
listed a single MZUN specimen numbered “606”. We also found 
<specimenCount id="F6CCFD3FFEDDFEBB5C0BF882FB286650" box="[1045,1179,1807,1833]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in this study. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FEDDFEBB58D9F8BFFE026634" author="Rondani, C." box="[199,433,1842,1869]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 63)</bibRefCitation>
only gave the type locality as “ 
<collectingCountry id="98DD7626FEDDFEBB5B0FF8BFFCD46635" box="[785,871,1842,1868]" name="Brazil" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Brasile</collectingCountry>
”, 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FEDDFEBB5B63F8BEFBC36635" author="Papavero, N." box="[893,1136,1842,1869]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" refId="ref362581" refString="Papavero, N. (1973) Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology, with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. 2. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paolo, Sao Paolo, pp. 217 - 446." type="book" year="1973">Papavero (1973: 343)</bibRefCitation>
gave a more accurate type locality based on a note in 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FEDDFEBB59E8F8DBFD2E6608" author="Spinola, M." box="[502,669,1878,1905]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="19 - 94" refId="ref374743" refString="Spinola, M. (1853) Compte rendu des hymenopteres inedits provenants du voyage entomologique de M. Ghiliani dans le Para en 1846. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Series 2, 13, 19 - 94." type="journal article" year="1853">Spinola (1853)</bibRefCitation>
that said all specimens collected by Ghiliani in 1846 were collected in Belem, Pará, 
<collectingCountry id="98DD7626FEDDFEBB5965F8F7FE7066ED" box="[379,451,1914,1940]" name="Brazil" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
